        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-20 09:04:54.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\nWhile testing alpine based image I've found that project uses embedded MongoDB which cannot be run without glibc installed. Adding glibc to alpine requires building it from sources and final image size will be ~350Mb vs. 470Mb in case of ubuntu based image. Moreover, building glibc from sources takes noticeable amount of time even on powerful machine. Thus, it doesn't worth it to move this app image to alpine.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "78dda866918810b2efc7fc38424a6d9d674f64c6",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5040,
          "name": "Dmitrii Puzikov",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "d.puzikov2@partner.samsung.com",
          "username": "dpuzikov"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-20 09:17:26.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: -Code-Review\n\nAnother one issue found: de.flapdoodle.embed.mongo plugin used for getting embedded mongodb doesn't support non-amd64 cpu architectures. Some investigation shows that nongodb itself support arm64, s390 architectures but plugin has amd64 hardcoded. Similar maven plugins are based on the mentioned de.flapdoodle.embed.mongo plugin and don't support multi-arch too. I'm looking for acceptable solution at the moment.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
